definition.value: a hematology investigation result abnormal AE that has an outcome of a positive coombs test, which is a blood test that identifies the causes of anemia
a behavior and neurological AE that results in a loss of coordination
a coronary artery disorder AE that has an outcome of an blockage in the coronary artery
a coronary artery disorder AE that has an outcome of an insufficient amount of blood circulates through the coronary arteries
a tumor AE that has an outcome of a brain tumor derived from the embryonic tissue of the pituitary gland
a c-reactive protein level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased amount of CRP, a protein that measure general levels of inflammation in the body
a nervous system AE that has an outcome of increased pressure in the skull
a urine analysis result abnormal AE that has an outcome of high bacterial colonization counts in the urine
an inflammation AE that has an outcome of inflamed blood vessels in the skin

a urinary system AE that has an outcome of cystitis with severe hemorrhage, a dose-limiting toxic condition with administration of ifosfamide and cyclophosphamide or a complication of bone marrow transplantation
a genetic disorder AE that has an outcome of an atypical number of chromosomes or a structural abnormality in one or more chromosomes
an inflammation AE that has an outcome of release of cytokines by T cells that causes inflammation

an inflammation AE that results in the inflammation of the colon
a viral infection AE that is caused by cytomegalovirus
a skin AE that has an outcome of shedding of the dead skin cells from the scalp

a venous thrombosis that is characterized by a blood clot that forms in a vein deep in the body. Blood clots occur when blood thickens and clumps together. Most deep vein blood clots occur in the lower leg or thigh. They also can occur in other parts of the body.
a psychiatric disorder AE that results in a decline in level of cognitive function

a sensory capability AE that results in a lower level of arousal than normal
a dermatitis ae that is characterized by the eruption of papules and pustules, typically on the face, scalp, upper chest and back.

a muscle AE that has an outcome of muscle weakness, inflammation, skin rash and difficulty swallowing
a motor neuropathy AE that has an outcome of poor coordination
an injury and procedural complication AE that results in the dislocation of a device

an injury and procedural complication AE that results in an infection related to medical device
a coma AE which is induced by the condition that the patient has extremely high levels of sugar in the blood without ketones
a respiratory system AE that has an outcome of an abnormal hole in the diaphragm
a paralysis AE that has an outcome of a paralyzed diaphragm
a diarrhea AE that has an outcome of rectal bleeding and bloody diarrhea
a diarrhea AE that has an outcome of diarrhea is caused by infection
a cardiac disorder AE with an outcome of decline in performance of one or both ventricles of the heart during the time phase of diastole, when heart filling with incoming blood
a cardiac ventricular disorder AE that has an outcome of enlargement of a heart chamber that pumps blood away from the heart
an adverse event with an outcome of worsening of the disease
a bone disorder AE that has an outcome of dislocation of vertebra
a sensory capability AE that results in the senses of time, direction, and recognition of people and places becoming difficult to distinguish
a hematopoietic system AE with an outcome of a serious disorder in which proteins that control blood clotting become abnormally active
a behavior and neurological AE that results in a loss of attention

a hemorrhage AE that has an outcome of bleeding in the intestine due to diverticulitis
an adverse event that has an outcome of a decreased amount of the drug excreted by the body
an adverse drug event that results in the development of a dependence on the drug
a skin AE that has an outcome of a range of adverse drugs reactions of the skin, most commonly rashes resembling measles
a hypersensitivity AE that has an outcome of allergic reactions to certain drugs

a headache AE that has an outcome of headaches due to drug withdrawal
